Detailed Description

Function Documentation

◆ json_create()

cosmosstruc * json_create ( )

Initialize JSON pointer map.

Create a cosmosstruc and use it to assign storage for each of the groups and entries for each of the non Node based elements to the JSON Name Map.

Returns
Pointer to new cosmosstruc or nullptr.
86 {
87  // extern char etext;
88  cosmosstruc *cinfo = nullptr;
89  unitstruc tunit;
90 
91  if ((cinfo = new cosmosstruc) == nullptr)
92  {
93  return nullptr;
94  }
95 
96  // Make sure it's clear
97  // memset(cinfo, 0, sizeof(cosmosstruc));
98 
99  // cinfo->jmapbase = &etext;
100  cinfo->jmapped = 0;
101  cinfo->unit.resize(JSON_UNIT_COUNT);
102  // cinfo->target.resize(100);
103  cinfo->jmap.resize(JSON_MAX_HASH);
104  cinfo->emap.resize(JSON_MAX_HASH);
105 
106  // Make sure we aren't running out of memory
107  if (cinfo->unit.size() != JSON_UNIT_COUNT ||
108  cinfo->jmap.size() != JSON_MAX_HASH ||
109  cinfo->emap.size() != JSON_MAX_HASH)
110  {
111  delete [] cinfo;
112  return nullptr;
113  }
114 
115  cinfo->glossary.resize(1);
116  cinfo->agent.resize(1);
117  cinfo->event.resize(1);
118  cinfo->user.resize(1);
119  memset(&cinfo->node, 0, sizeof(nodestruc));
120  memset(&cinfo->physics, 0, sizeof(physicsstruc));
121  memset(&cinfo->devspec, 0, sizeof(devspecstruc));
122 
123  // Make sure we aren't running out of memory
124  if (cinfo->glossary.size() != 1 ||
125  cinfo->agent.size() != 1 ||
126  cinfo->event.size() != 1 ||
127  cinfo->user.size() != 1)
128  {
129  delete [] cinfo;
130  return nullptr;
131  }
132 
133  // Copy primary to secondary
134  // json_clone(cinfo->sdata);
135 
136  // Create JSON Map unit table
137  for (uint16_t i=0; i<cinfo->unit.size(); ++i)
138  {
139  // SI Units
140  tunit.type = JSON_UNIT_TYPE_IDENTITY;
141  tunit.p0 = tunit.p1 = tunit.p2 = 0.;
142  switch (i)
143  {
144  case JSON_UNIT_NONE:
145  tunit.name = "";
146  break;
147  case JSON_UNIT_ACCELERATION:
148  tunit.name = "m/s2";
149  break;
150  case JSON_UNIT_ANGLE:
151  tunit.name = "rad";
152  break;
153  case JSON_UNIT_ANGULAR_RATE:
154  tunit.name = "rad/s";
155  break;
156  case JSON_UNIT_AREA:
157  tunit.name = "m2";
158  break;
159  case JSON_UNIT_BYTES:
160  tunit.name = "GiB";
161  break;
162  case JSON_UNIT_CAPACITANCE:
163  tunit.name = "F";
164  break;
165  case JSON_UNIT_CHARGE:
166  tunit.name = "C";
167  break;
168  case JSON_UNIT_CURRENT:
169  tunit.name = "A";
170  break;
171  case JSON_UNIT_DATE:
172  tunit.name = "MJD";
173  break;
174  case JSON_UNIT_DENSITY:
175  tunit.name = "kg/m3";
176  break;
177  case JSON_UNIT_ENERGY:
178  tunit.name = "j";
179  break;
180  case JSON_UNIT_FORCE:
181  tunit.name = "N";
182  break;
183  case JSON_UNIT_FRACTION:
184  tunit.name = "";
185  break;
186  case JSON_UNIT_FREQUENCY:

492  uint16_t hashval;

int32_t json_addentry ( string  alias,
string  value,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo 
)

Enter an alias into the JSON Namespace.

See if the provided name is in the Namespace. If so, add an entry for the provided alias that points to the same location.

Parameters
aliasName to add as an alias.
valueEither the contents of an equation, or a Namespace name that should already exist in the Namespace
cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
Returns
The current number of entries, if successful, otherwise negative error.
513 {
514  int32_t iretn;
515  jsonhandle handle;
516  // uint16_t count = 0;
517  // Add this alias only if it is not already in the map
518  if ((iretn = json_name_map(alias, cinfo, handle)))
519  {
520  jsonentry tentry;
521  tentry.name = alias;
522  aliasstruc talias;
523  talias.name = alias;
524  // If it begins with ( then it is an equation, otherwise treat as name
525  switch (value[0])
526  {
527  case '(':
528  // Add new equation
529  iretn = json_equation_map(value, cinfo, &handle);
530  if (iretn < 0)
531  {
532  return iretn;
533  }
534  talias.handle = handle;
535  talias.type = JSON_TYPE_EQUATION;
536  break;
537  default:
538  // It is a Namespace name which should only be added if it is in the map
539  if ((iretn = json_name_map(value, cinfo, handle)))
540  {

542  }

545  talias.type = cinfo->jmap[handle.hash][handle.index].type;

552  tentry.group = JSON_STRUCT_PTR;

555  iretn = json_addentry(tentry, cinfo);
556  if (iretn < 0)

558  return iretn;
559  }
560  }

int32_t json_addentry ( jsonentry  entry,

)

Enter an entry into the JSON Namespace.

Enters a jsonentry in the JSON Data Name Space.

Parameters
entryThe entry to be entered.
cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
Returns

572 {
573  uint16_t hash = json_hash(entry.name);
574  size_t csize = cinfo->jmap[hash].size();

576  for (size_t i=0; i<csize; ++i)
577  {

int32_t json_addentry ( string  name,

)

Add an entry to the JSON Namespace map with units.

Allocates the space for a new jsonentry and then enters the information associating a pointer with an entry in the name table. The name will be of form "name" if it is a scalar, "name_iii" if it is a first level array, "name_iii_iii" if it is second level, where "iii" is the zero filled index for the appropriate level.

Parameters
namevariable name from the JSON Data Name Space
d1array index for first level, otherwise -1
d2array index for second level, otherwise -1
offsetOffset to the data from the beginning of its group.
sizeNumber of bytes jsonentry take up.
typeCOSMOS JSON Data Type.
groupCOSMOS JSON Data Group.
cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
unitIndex into JMAP unit table.
Returns
The current number of entries, if successful, 0 if the entry could not be added, or if enough memory could not be allocated to hold the JSON stream.
613 {

615  char ename[COSMOS_MAX_NAME+1];
616

620  sprintf(&ename[strlen(ename)],"_%03u",d1);
621  if (d2 < UINT16_MAX)
622  sprintf(&ename[strlen(ename)],"_%03u",d2);
623 
624  // Populate the entry

626  tentry.alert_index = 0;
627  tentry.maximum_index = 0;

int32_t json_out_string ( string &  jstring,
string  ostring,

)

String to JSON.

Appends a JSON entry to the current JSON stream for the string variable.

Parameters

1257

1259  len = JSON_MAX_DATA;
1260

1262  return (iretn);

1265  {

1268  break;
1269  }

1300  case '\t':

1302  return (iretn);
1303  break;
1304  default:

1306  return (iretn);
1307  sprintf(tstring,"%04x", ostring[i]);
1308  if ((iretn=json_out_string(jstring,tstring,4)) < 0)
1309  return (iretn);
1310  }
1311  }
1312  else if (ostring[i] < 127)
1313  {
1314  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring, ostring[i])) < 0)
1315  return (iretn);
1316  }
1317  else
1318  {
1319  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'\\')) < 0)
1320  return (iretn);
1321  if ((iretn=json_out_character(jstring,'u')) < 0)
1322  return (iretn);
1323  sprintf(tstring,"%04x", ostring[i]);
1324  if ((iretn=json_out_string(jstring,tstring,4)) < 0)
1325  return (iretn);
1326  }
1327  }

1329  return (iretn);

◆ json_equation() [1/3]

double json_equation ( const char *&  ptr,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo 
)

Return the results of a JSON equation.

At its minimum, a JSON equation will be defined as any two JSON names separated by an operation. Equations bracketed by '()' will be treated as names in their own right and will therefore require a matching operation, and name or bracketed equation. The result will always be assumed to be double precision, even in the case of booleans. Valid operations are:

  • '!': logical NOT
  • '~': bitwise complement
  • '+': addition
  • '-': subtraction
  • '*': multiplication
  • '/': division
  • '': modulo
  • '&': logical AND
  • '|': logical OR
  • '>': logical Greater Than
  • '<': logical Less Than
  • '=': logical Equal
  • '^': power
    Parameters
    ptrPointer to a pointer to a JSON stream.
    cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
    cdataReference to cosmosdatastruc to use.
    Returns
    Result of the equation, or NAN.

4079  return (NAN);
4080

4082  return (NAN);
4083 
4084  if ((iretn=json_equation_map(equation, cinfo, &handle)) < 0)
4085  {
4086  return (NAN);
4087  }
4088

◆ json_clear_cosmosstruc()

int32_t json_clear_cosmosstruc ( int32_t  type,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo 
)

Clear global data structure.

Zero out elements of the cosmosstruc. The entire structure can be cleared, or the clearing can be confined to either the Dynamic or Static piece. This allows you to remove the effects of previous calls to json_parse.

Parameters
typeInstance of JSON_STRUCT_* enumeration.
cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
cdataReference to cosmosdatastruc to use.
Returns
0, or a negative COSMOS Error codes.

int32_t json_load_node ( string  node,
jsonnode &  json 
)

Map Name Space to global data structure components and pieces.

Create an entry in the JSON mapping tables between each name in the Name Space and the cosmosstruc.

Parameters
nodeName and/or path of node directory. If name, then a path will be created based on nodedir setting. If path, then name will be extracted from the end.
jsonjsonnode for storing JSON.
Returns
0, or a negative value from COSMOS Error Code definitions.

◆ json_recenter_node()

int32_t json_recenter_node ( cosmosstruc *  cinfo)
6324 {
6325  // Calculate centroid, normal and area for each face
6326  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->faces.size(); ++i)
6327  {
6328  if (cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt)
6329  {
6330  Vector fcentroid = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]];
6331  fcentroid += cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[1]];
6332  Vector v1 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt-1]];
6333  Vector v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[1]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]];
6334  Vector fnormal = v1.cross(v2);
6335  for (size_t j=2; j<cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt; ++j)
6336  {
6337  fcentroid += cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j]];
6338  v1 = v2;
6339  v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j-1]];
6340  fnormal += v1.cross(v2);
6341  }
6342  v1 = v2;
6343  v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[0]] - cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt-1]];
6344  fnormal += v1.cross(v2);
6345 
6346  fcentroid /= cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt;
6347  cinfo->faces[i].normal = fnormal.normalize();
6348 
6349  cinfo->faces[i].com = Math::Vector();
6350  cinfo->faces[i].area = 0.;
6351  v1 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt-1]] - fcentroid;
6352  for (size_t j=0; j<cinfo->faces[i].vertex_cnt; ++j)
6353  {
6354  v2 = cinfo->vertexs[cinfo->faces[i].vertex_idx[j]] - fcentroid;
6355  // Area of triangle made by v1, v2 and Face centroid
6356  double tarea = v1.area(v2);
6357  // Sum
6358  cinfo->faces[i].area += tarea;
6359  // Centroid of triangle made by v1, v2 amd Face centroid
6360  Vector tcentroid = (v1 + v2 + fcentroid) / 3.;
6361  // Weighted sum
6362  cinfo->faces[i].com += tcentroid * tarea;
6363  v1 = v2;
6364  }
6365  // Divide by summed weights
6366  if (cinfo->faces[i].area)
6367  {
6368  cinfo->faces[i].com /= cinfo->faces[i].area;
6369  }
6370  }
6371  }
6372 
6373  Vector tcom = Vector();
6374  double tvolume = 0.;
6375  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->pieces.size(); ++i)
6376  {
6377  // Clean up any missing faces and calculate center of mass for each Piece using Faces
6378  cinfo->pieces[i].com = Math::Vector();
6379  for (size_t j=0; j<cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt; ++j)
6380  {
6381  if (cinfo->faces.size() <= cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])
6382  {
6383  cinfo->faces.resize(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]+1);
6384  cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].com = Math::Vector();
6385  cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].area = 0.;
6386  cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].normal = Math::Vector();
6387  }
6388  cinfo->pieces[i].com += cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j]].com;
6389  }
6390  if (cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt)
6391  {
6392  cinfo->pieces[i].com /= cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt;
6393  }
6394 
6395  // Calculate volume for each Piece using center of mass for each Face
6396  // Calculate normal for each Face that faces away from center of piece, or center of object
6397  cinfo->pieces[i].volume = 0.;
6398  for (size_t j=0; j<cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt; ++j)
6399  {
6400  Vector dv = cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])].com - cinfo->pieces[i].com;
6401  if (dv.norm() != 0.)
6402  {
6403  cinfo->pieces[i].volume += cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])].area * dv.norm() / 3.;
6404  double sepangle = dv.separation(cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])].normal);
6405 // double msepangle = dv.separation(cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])].normal * -1.);
6406  if (sepangle > DPI2)
6407  {
6408  if (cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j] < cinfo->faces.size())
6409  {
6410  facestruc tface = cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])];
6411  tface.normal *= -1.;
6412  for (size_t k=0; k<tface.vertex_idx.size(); ++k)
6413  {
6414  tface.vertex_idx[k] = cinfo->faces[(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j])].vertex_idx[tface.vertex_idx.size()-(k+1)];
6415  }
6416  cinfo->faces.push_back(tface);
6417  cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[j] = cinfo->faces.size() - 1;
6418  }
6419  }
6420  }
6421  }
6422  cinfo->node.face_cnt = cinfo->faces.size();
6423  tvolume += cinfo->pieces[i].volume;
6424  tcom += cinfo->pieces[i].com * cinfo->pieces[i].volume;
6425  }
6426  if (tvolume)
6427  {
6428  tcom /= tvolume;
6429  }
6430 
6431  // Calculate special norm for external panels
6432  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->pieces.size(); ++i)
6433  {
6434  if (cinfo->pieces[i].face_cnt == 1)
6435  {
6436  Vector dv = cinfo->faces[abs(cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0])].com - tcom;
6437  if (dv.separation(cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0]].normal) > DPI2)
6438  {
6439  cinfo->normals.push_back(-cinfo->faces[cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0]].normal);
6440  cinfo->pieces[i].face_idx[0] = cinfo->normals.size() - 1;
6441  }
6442  }
6443  }
6444 
6445  // Recenter all vectors to object center of mass
6446  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->vertexs.size(); ++i)
6447  {
6448  cinfo->vertexs[i] -= tcom;
6449  }
6450 
6451  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->faces.size(); ++i)
6452  {
6453  cinfo->faces[i].com -= tcom;
6454  cinfo->faces[i].normal -= tcom;
6455  }
6456 
6457  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->pieces.size(); ++i)
6458  {
6459  cinfo->pieces[i].com -= tcom;
6460  }
6461  return 0;
6462 }

◆ json_setup_node() [1/2]

int32_t json_setup_node ( jsonnode  json,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo,
bool  create_flag 
)

Setup JSON Namespace using Node description JSON.

Create an entry in the JSON mapping tables between each name in the Name Space and the cosmosstruc. Load descriptive information from a structure of JSON descriptions.

Parameters
jsonStructure containing JSON descriptions.
cinfoPointer to cinfo cosmosstruc.
create_flagWhether or not to create node directory if it doesn't already exist.
Returns
0, or a negative COSMOS Error Code definitions

Load targeting information

◆ json_toggledeviceentry()

int32_t json_toggledeviceentry ( uint16_t  type,
uint16_t  didx,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo,
bool  state 
)

Toggle device entry.

Toggle the enable state of the entries specific to device number i in the JSON Namespace map.

Parameters
typeDevice type number taken from DeviceType.
didxDevice number.
cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
stateDesired enable state.
Returns
0 or negative error.

10267  cinfo->node.com.col[2] += cinfo->pieces[cinfo->device[n].all.pidx].centroid.col[2] * cinfo->device[n].all.mass;
10268  }
10269  if (cinfo->device[n].all.pidx >= 0)
10270  {
10271  cinfo->pieces[cinfo->device[n].all.pidx].heat += 300. * cinfo->pieces[cinfo->device[n].all.pidx].hcap * cinfo->device[n].all.mass;
10272  cinfo->node.heat += 300. * cinfo->pieces[cinfo->device[n].all.pidx].hcap * cinfo->device[n].all.mass;
10273  }
10274  cinfo->node.mass += cinfo->device[n].all.mass;
10275  */
10276  cinfo->device[n].all.temp = 300.;
10277  // cinfo->device[n].all.flag |= DEVICE_FLAG_ON;
10278  if (cinfo->device[n].all.flag & DEVICE_FLAG_ON)
10279  {
10280  cinfo->device[n].all.amp = cinfo->device[n].all.namp;
10281  cinfo->device[n].all.volt = cinfo->device[n].all.nvolt;
10282  cinfo->device[n].all.power = cinfo->device[n].all.amp * cinfo->device[n].all.volt;
10283  }
10284  if (cinfo->device[n].all.bidx < cinfo->devspec.bus_cnt && cinfo->devspec.bus[cinfo->device[n].all.bidx]->volt < cinfo->device[n].all.volt)
10285  {
10286  cinfo->devspec.bus[cinfo->device[n].all.bidx]->volt = cinfo->device[n].all.volt;
10287  }
10288  }
10289 
10290  // cinfo->physics.com = rv_smult(1./cinfo->physics.mass,cinfo->physics.com);
10291  cinfo->physics.hcap /= cinfo->physics.mass;
10292 
10293  for (size_t n=0; n<cinfo->pieces.size(); n++)
10294  {
10295  piecestruc *tpiece = &cinfo->pieces[n];
10296  tpiece->shove = Vector();
10297  tpiece->twist = Vector();
10298  switch (cinfo->pieces[n].face_cnt)
10299  {
10300  default:
10301  {
10302  double ta = tpiece->com.flattenx().norm();
10303  cinfo->physics.moi.x += tpiece->mass * ta * ta;
10304  ta = tpiece->com.flatteny().norm();
10305  cinfo->physics.moi.y += tpiece->mass * ta * ta;
10306  ta = tpiece->com.flattenz().norm();
10307  cinfo->physics.moi.z += tpiece->mass * ta * ta;
10308  }
10309  break;
10310  case 1:
10311  {
10312  tpiece->shove = -tpiece->area * (cinfo->faces[tpiece->face_idx[0]].normal.dot(tpiece->com)) * tpiece->com / (tpiece->com.norm() * tpiece->com.norm());
10313  tpiece->twist = -tpiece->area * tpiece->com.norm() * cinfo->faces[tpiece->face_idx[0]].normal - tpiece->com.norm() * tpiece->shove;
10314  }
10315  break;
10316  case 0:
10317  break;
10318  }
10319  }
10320 
10321  if (length_rv(cinfo->node.moi) == 0.)
10322  {
10323  cinfo->node.moi = cinfo->physics.moi.to_rv();
10324  }
10325  else
10326  {
10327  cinfo->physics.moi = cinfo->node.moi;
10328  }
10329 
10330  // Turn all CPU's on
10331  for (size_t n=0; n<cinfo->devspec.cpu_cnt; n++)
10332  {
10333  cinfo->device[cinfo->devspec.cpu[n]->cidx].all.flag |= DEVICE_FLAG_ON;
10334  }
10335 
10336  // Turn on all IMU's
10337  for (size_t n=0; n<cinfo->devspec.imu_cnt; n++)
10338  {
10339  cinfo->device[cinfo->devspec.imu[n]->cidx].all.flag |= DEVICE_FLAG_ON;
10340  }
10341 
10342  // Turn on all GPS's
10343  for (size_t n=0; n<cinfo->devspec.gps_cnt; n++)
10344  {
10345  cinfo->device[cinfo->devspec.gps[n]->cidx].all.flag |= DEVICE_FLAG_ON;
10346  }
10347 
10348  cinfo->node.battcap = 0.;
10349  for (size_t n=0; n<cinfo->devspec.batt_cnt; n++)
10350  {
10351  cinfo->node.battcap += cinfo->devspec.batt[n]->capacity;
10352  cinfo->devspec.batt[n]->charge = cinfo->devspec.batt[n]->capacity;
10353  }
10354  cinfo->node.battlev = cinfo->node.battcap;
10355 
10356  // Turn off reaction wheels
10357  for (size_t i=0; i<cinfo->devspec.rw_cnt; i++)
10358  {
10359  cinfo->devspec.rw[i]->alp = cinfo->devspec.rw[i]->omg = 0.;
10360  }
10361 
10362  // Set fictional torque to zero
10363  cinfo->physics.ftorque = rv_zero();
10364 
10365  return 0;
10366 }

◆ create_databases()

void create_databases ( cosmosstruc *  cinfo)

Dump tab delimited database files.

Create files that can be read in to a relational database representing the various elements of the satellite. Tables are created for Parts, Components, Devices, Temperature Sensors and Power Buses.

size_t load_dictionary ( vector< shorteventstruc > &  dict,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo,

)

Load Event Dictionary.

Read a specific event dictionary for a specific node. The dictionary is stored as multiple condition based JSON event strings in a file of the specified name, in the cinfo directory of the specified node. The result is a vector of event structures.

Parameters
dictReference to vector of shorteventstruc.
cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
cdataReference to cosmosdatastruc to use.
fileName of dictionary file.
Returns
Number of items loaded.
10679 {
10680  FILE *op;
10681  char inb[JSON_MAX_DATA];
10682  shorteventstruc sevent;
10683  jsonhandle handle;
10684  int32_t iretn;
10685 
10686  string fname = (get_nodedir(cinfo->node.name) + "/") + file;
10687  if ((op=fopen(fname.c_str(),"r")) != NULL)
10688  {
10689  while (fgets(inb,JSON_MAX_DATA,op) != NULL)
10690  {
10691  json_clear_cosmosstruc(JSON_STRUCT_EVENT, cinfo);
10692  if (json_parse(inb, cinfo) >= 0)
10693  {
10694  if ((iretn=json_equation_map(cinfo->event[0].l.condition, cinfo, &handle)) < 0)
10695  continue;
10696  sevent = cinfo->event[0].s;
10697  sevent.utcexec = 0.;
10698  sevent.handle = handle;
10699  dict.push_back(sevent);
10700  }
10701  }
10702  fclose(op);
10703  dict.shrink_to_fit();
10704  return (dict.size());
10705  }
10706  else
10707  return 0;
10708 }

◆ calc_events()

size_t calc_events ( vector< shorteventstruc > &  dictionary,
cosmosstruc *  cinfo,
vector< shorteventstruc > &  events 
)

Calculate current Events.

Using the provided Event Dictionary, calculate all the Events for current state of the provided Node. The Event Dictionary will be updated with any new values so that repeating Events can be properly assessed.

Parameters
dictionaryReference to vector of shorteventstruc representing event dictionary.
cmetaReference to cosmosmetastruc to use.
cdataReference to cosmosdatastruc to use.
eventsReference to vector of shorteventstruc representing events.

10722 {
10723  double value;
10724  // const char *cp;
10725  char *sptr, *eptr;
10726 
10727  events.resize(0);
10728  for (uint32_t k=0; k<dictionary.size(); ++k)
10729  {
10730  if (!std::isnan(value=json_equation(&dictionary[k].handle, cinfo)) && value != 0. && dictionary[k].value == 0.)
10731  {
10732  dictionary[k].utc = cinfo->node.loc.utc;
10733  events.push_back(dictionary[k]);
10734  string tstring = json_get_string(dictionary[k].data, cinfo);
10735  strcpy(events[events.size()-1].data, tstring.c_str());
10736  strcpy(events[events.size()-1].node,cinfo->node.name);
10737  if ((sptr=strstr(events[events.size()-1].name,"${")) != NULL && (eptr=strstr(sptr,"}")) != NULL)
10738  {
10739  *eptr = 0;
10740  tstring = json_get_string(sptr+2, cinfo);
10741  strcpy(sptr, tstring.c_str());
10742  }
10743  }
10744  dictionary[k].value = value;
10745  }
10746 
10747  events.shrink_to_fit();
10748  return (events.size());
10749 }
